---
export const prerender = true

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="About - Christopher Harley"
  description="About Christopher Harley, Design Engineer"
>
  <section
    class="max-w-max-width mx-auto px-edge-padding pb-section-v-space flex flex-col gap-section-v-space mb-section-v-space mt-section-v-space"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-gutter items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-5 relative w-full aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden">
        <img
          alt="Christopher Harley Portrait"
          class="w-full h-full object-cover grayscale"
          src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aida-public/AB6AXuAfZGvrN5Z9O4GHz-ysdSHcwYLDzkzuz7SUwOUpAnPn0hweh1rdDshJrCKW20poqnkoP-CRldHWgTeDInDGBRsXGV0Oa5v21b6dK-nbx4Fn2ba3CTW7JkZaiZadjYimJxalwIS0SkohbcF9hUzDxYAz9hynE-XbCSBrr-dRjsgVjO96Z7retW15eVhzheDYZE9Gr3koudSlCMdaBXCUu_gx3BQxVM4S7PrUQHlb29GOvckBlDD5C6dudQ2jD3gmBzjDzwJ0XyIOCsw"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-7 flex flex-col pt-8 md:pt-0">
        <h1 class="font-headline-lg text-headline-lg text-text-primary mb-unit">
          Christopher Harley
        </h1>
        <div
          class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary font-body-lg text-body-lg max-w-prose mb-12"
        >
          <p>
            I'm a creative technologist who fell into web development while
            learning to code and stayed for the design. What started as
            curiosity about how websites worked quickly became a fascination
            with how they <em>felt</em> — the whitespace, the rhythm, the subtle details
            that make something feel right. That pull toward the visual side led me
            deep into UI/UX design, and for the last six years I've been moving between
            design and development, always chasing that intersection where beauty
            meets function.
          </p>
          <p>
            Beyond the screen, my work is heavily influenced by the
            compositional rigor of electronic music and minimalist editorial
            design. I believe that removing visual noise allows the true intent
            of an interface to emerge, transforming functional tools into quiet,
            confident experiences.
          </p>
          <p>
            Currently exploring the intersection of generative models and
            precise layout systems, striving to build interfaces that feel
            engineered rather than merely decorated.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start sm:items-center mt-auto border-t border-border-muted/30 pt-8"
        >
          <a
            href="#"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-outline bg-transparent hover:bg-surface-container-low hover:border-text-primary transition-colors duration-200 text-text-primary"
          >
            <span class="font-label-mono text-label-mono mr-2"
              >Download Resume (PDF)</span
            >
            <span
              class="material-symbols-outlined"
              style="font-variation-settings: 'FILL' 0;">download</span
            >
          </a>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="font-label-mono text-label-mono text-text-primary hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-200 flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            Get in touch
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[16px]"
              >arrow_forward</span
            >
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
